As part of the Nanoelectronics & Nanotechnology Group, contributed to the design of a memory buffer circuit for an industry partner, focusing on readout circuitry looking at reliability and area efficiency.

Additionally, contributed to testing digital circuits, checking the full design flow from RTL to layout to ensure functionality and seamless integration.

Verified pad functionality and pin orientation for full-chip integration, supporting a padring with over 230 pins.

Gained hands-on experience in circuit design, reliability analysis, and physical implementation, bridging academic research with real-world industry applications.
